formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1. Carpet area provided in certificate is as provided to me by project promoter in consultation with project architect at the time of registration of project.
2. Inadvertently at the time of project registration, I have provided RERA collection account number (008505004039) as RERA account number. In fact RERA account number is 008505004040. Consider 008505004040 as RERA account number for this certificate instead of 008505004039, as provided in certificate and at the time of registration of project. Details of deposit & withdrawal provided in certificate is of RERA account (008505004040) and not of 008505004039.
3. Promoter of project received sale proceeds without first entering in agreement for sale. However it was found while verifying books and other documents that promoter first sold units (Flat) through registered sale deed and after that received amount mentioned therein. No advance/booking amount taken from buyer(s) before flat(s) were sold. 
4. Promoter raised and used unsecured loan and CC account with The VVCC Bank Limited for making various project payments. However due to general borrowing of nature of loans, it is not possible for me to provide required details of loan in certificate. In fact promoter used Loan/borrowing  for making  various project payments.     
5. Promoter of project run two project simultaneously (Tower - A+ Tower -B), and does not maintain separate set of books of account hence in details of actual construction cost incurred and paid column of certificate, I have provided details of those payments as certified by promoter that he had made for this project (i.e Tower-A).

physProgressList.reason: As per promoter explanation, project engineer at the time of registration of project estimated very high construction cost hence there is vital difference in cost of construction incurred as per engineer form-2 as compare to actual construction cost incurred and paid as per books of accounts.
